  "description": "Progression from first ICs to complex VLSI chips via Moore's Law-like scaling: wafer size increases (2\" to 12\"), feature size shrinks (10 μm to 7 nm), layer count grows (1-2 to 10+), and yield improves (10% to 90%+). Each generation doubles transistor count while requiring larger crystal pullers, better process uniformity, and advanced lithography equipment.",
